==German==

===Etymology===
From the from [[gelten]] (''to be valid'').

===Adverb===
'''gell'''
# {{slang}} a [[w:Tag question|tag question]] roughly [[equivalent]] to ''yes?'', ''no?'', ''isn't that so?'', ''[[innit]]''
#: ''Wir gehen, '''gell'''?''
#:: ''We're going, '''aren't we'''?''

===Usage notes===
The word is generally restricted to South German speech.

